SIMPLE: unciform
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unciform
<hw>Un"ci*form</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n"s⟦icr⟧*f⟦ocir⟧rm)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>uncus</ets> a hook + <ets>-form</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having
the shape of a hook; being of a curved or hooked form;
hooklike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Unciform bone</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>a bone of
the carpus at the bases of the fourth and fifth metacarpals; the
hamatum.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unciform</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unciform
<hw>Un"ci*form</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The unciform
bone. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Perissodactyla</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncinata</ent>⟦br⟧
